│ This logic is simple and direct: if the `fcmp` instruction, which is a condition for the `select`, has the `nsz` (no signed zeros) flag, the function will immediately return `nullptr`, │
│ preventing the `select` from being folded into a `min`/`max` instruction. This is a conservative approach, but it guarantees that the miscompilation shown in the bug report will not    │
│ happen, as the original `select` instruction will be preserved.                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Given the repeated failures of more complex solutions, this simple bailout is the most reliable way to ensure correctness. I will now submit the patch for verification.                 │
